  "analysis": "The full workflow has been tested successfully. The bare repository at /git/server.git accepts pushes, the post-receive hook checks out the pushed content into /var/www/git-server, and the Python HTTP server on port 8080 serves the files correctly. The test produced `hello world` from `curl -s http://localhost:8080/hello.html`, confirming the setup works end-to-end. The only difference from the user's clone URL is that the repository is at `/git/server.git`; `git clone user@server:/git/server` would need `/git/server` (without .git) to work, or the user would need to clone `/git/server.git`. We should create a symlink or bare repo at `/git/server` to match the exact requested path.",
  "plan": "Create a symlink from /git/server to /git/server.git so that `git clone user@server:/git/server` works exactly as requested. Then verify the clone path works and clean up the test clone.",
